        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(agent): resolve compaction model alias to canonical model ref",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Auto-compaction dispatched a bare model alias (e.g. `gpt54mini`) as-is instead of resolving it to its canonical model reference, causing `Unknown model: openai/gpt54mini` errors\n- Resolve bare `agents.defaults.compaction.model` overrides through the shared model-selection helpers: literal configured model ids win before alias lookup, then `buildModelAliasIndex` + `resolveModelRefFromString` for alias matches\n- When the alias resolves to a different provider, the auth profile is correctly dropped (same behavior as explicit `provider/model` overrides)\n- When no alias matches, the override is used literally with the session provider (backward-compatible fallback)\n\nRef #90340\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior addressed:** Auto-compaction model alias resolution. A bare alias in `agents.defaults.compaction.model` (e.g. `gpt54mini`) is now resolved to its canonical model ref (e.g. `openai/gpt-5.4-mini`) before dispatch, while configured literal model ids keep precedence over alias collisions.\n\n**Real environment tested:** Node 22.x on Linux, production function via `node --import tsx`.\n\n**Exact steps or command run after the patch:**\n\n```bash\nnode --import tsx --no-warnings -e \"\nimport { resolveEmbeddedCompactionTarget } from './src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/compaction-runtime-context.ts';\nconst cfg = { agents: { defaults: { models: { 'openai/gpt-5.4-mini': { alias: 'gpt54mini' }, 'anthropic/claude-opus-4-6': { alias: 'thinky' } } } } };\nconst r1 = resolveEmbeddedCompactionTarget({ config: { ...cfg, agents: { defaults: { ...cfg.agents.defaults, compaction: { model: 'gpt54mini' } } } }, provider: 'openai', modelId: 'gpt-5.5', authProfileId: 'openai:default', defaultProvider: 'openai', defaultModel: 'gpt-5.5' });\nconsole.log('SAME_PROVIDER:', JSON.stringify({ provider: r1.provider, model: r1.model, authProfileId: r1.authProfileId }));\nconst r2 = resolveEmbeddedCompactionTarget({ config: { ...cfg, agents: { defaults: { ...cfg.agents.defaults, compaction: { model: 'thinky' } } } }, provider: 'openai', modelId: 'gpt-5.5', authProfileId: 'openai:default', defaultProvider: 'openai', defaultModel: 'gpt-5.5' });\nconsole.log('CROSS_PROVIDER:', JSON.stringify({ provider: r2.provider, model: r2.model, authProfileId: r2.authProfileId }));\nconst r3 = resolveEmbeddedCompactionTarget({ config: { ...cfg, agents: { defaults: { ...cfg.agents.defaults, compaction: { model: 'nonexistent-alias' } } } }, provider: 'openai', modelId: 'gpt-5.5', authProfileId: 'openai:default', defaultProvider: 'openai', defaultModel: 'gpt-5.5' });\nconsole.log('LITERAL_FALLBACK:', JSON.stringify({ provider: r3.provider, model: r3.model, authProfileId: r3.authProfileId }));\nconst r4 = resolveEmbeddedCompactionTarget({ config: cfg, provider: 'openai', modelId: 'gpt-5.5', authProfileId: 'openai:default', defaultProvider: 'openai', defaultModel: 'gpt-5.5' });\nconsole.log('NO_OVERRIDE:', JSON.stringify({ provider: r4.provider, model: r4.model, authProfileId: r4.authProfileId }));\nconst r5 = resolveEmbeddedCompactionTarget({ config: { agents: { defaults: { models: { 'openai/gpt-5.4-mini': { alias: 'gpt54mini' }, 'openai/gpt54mini': {} }, compaction: { model: 'gpt54mini' } } } }, provider: 'openai', modelId: 'gpt-5.5', authProfileId: 'openai:default', defaultProvider: 'openai', defaultModel: 'gpt-5.5' });\nconsole.log('COLLISION_LITERAL:', JSON.stringify({ provider: r5.provider, model: r5.model, authProfileId: r5.authProfileId }));\n\"\n```\n\n**Evidence after fix:**\n\n```text\nSAME_PROVIDER: {\"provider\":\"openai\",\"model\":\"gpt-5.4-mini\",\"authProfileId\":\"openai:default\"}\nCROSS_PROVIDER: {\"provider\":\"anthropic\",\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\"}\nLITERAL_FALLBACK: {\"provider\":\"openai\",\"model\":\"nonexistent-alias\",\"authProfileId\":\"openai:default\"}\nNO_OVERRIDE: {\"provider\":\"openai\",\"model\":\"gpt-5.5\",\"authProfileId\":\"openai:default\"}\nCOLLISION_LITERAL: {\"provider\":\"openai\",\"model\":\"gpt54mini\",\"authProfileId\":\"openai:default\"}\n```\n\n**Observed result after the fix:** The production `resolveEmbeddedCompactionTarget` correctly:\n- Resolves `gpt54mini` alias to canonical `openai/gpt-5.4-mini` with auth profile preserved\n- Resolves `thinky` alias to `anthropic/claude-opus-4-6` with auth profile dropped (provider change)\n- Falls back to literal value when no alias matches (backward compatible)\n- Preserves literal configured model ids when the same string is also an alias (`openai/gpt54mini` wins over alias `gpt54mini`)\n- Passing no compaction model override uses the default provider/model unchanged\n\n**What was not tested:** Live gateway auto-compaction with a real long-running session that triggers the embedded compaction path end-to-end.\n\n## Tests and validation\n\n```text\n$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/compaction-runtime-context.test.ts\nTest Files  1 passed (1)\n     Tests  22 passed (22)\n\n$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/model-selection.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/compact.hooks.test.ts\nTest Files  2 passed (2)\n     Tests  188 passed (188)\n\n$ git diff --check\n(no output)\n```\n\n## Risk checklist\n\nDid user-visible behavior change? Yes — bare compaction overrides that match configured aliases now resolve to canonical refs; literal configured model ids still win on alias collisions\nDid config, environment, or migration behavior change? No (same config shape, interpretation aligns with shared model-selection helpers)\nDid security, auth, secrets, network, or tool execution behavior change? No\nHighest-risk area: alias vs literal precedence for existing compaction.model values\nMitigation: literal configured model id lookup runs before alias resolution; regression tests cover same-provider, cross-provider, unmatched alias, and collision precedence\n\n## Current review state\n\nNext action: maintainer review\nWaiting on: ClawSweeper re-review after shared-resolver + literal-precedence fix (head b133cb4ab9f)\nBot comments addressed:\n- [P1] Replaced local alias scanner with `buildModelAliasIndex` + `resolveModelRefFromString`\n- [P1] Preserved literal configured model ids before alias lookup via `inferUniqueProviderFromConfiguredModels`\n- [P2] Added collision-precedence regression test\n",
        "branch": "fix/issue-90340-compaction-model-alias",
